tournament.name: Open Qualifer La Guilde des TW

decks.notes: The deck focuses on utilizing Dihada's ability to manipulate opponent's hands and graveyards while assembling powerful combos to control the game. It includes various tutors and reanimation spells to bring out key threats like Emrakul or Elesh Norn. The deck also features powerful removal spells to disrupt opponents' strategies and protect your own game plan. The mana base is designed to support a wide range of colors to ensure smooth gameplay and enable casting of spells from any part of the deck. Overall, the strategy revolves around assembling combos, disrupting opponents, and utilizing Dihada's abilities to dominate the battlefield and emerge victorious in one-on-one duels.

The key concept of this deck revolves around aggressive play and disruption. The deck utilizes a mix of efficient removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Terminate, along with hand disruption cards like Thoughtseize and Inquisition of Kozilek, to disrupt the opponent's game plan. It also features powerful creatures such as Dragon's Rage Channeler, Seasoned Pyromancer, and Phyrexian Dragon Engine that can quickly apply pressure and generate card advantage. The deck further enhances its aggression with cards like Blood Moon to disrupt the opponent's mana base and Flame Slash to deal with pesky creatures. Overall, the deck aims to quickly establish board presence and disrupt the opponent's strategy to secure a victory in the early game.
